earch (for exact keyword matching). \\n\\nFor hybrid search, you can use multi-queries (e.g. BM25 + vector) and combine the results client-side with e.g. reciprocal-rank fusion.\\n\\n## BM25 Implementation\\n\\nFull-text search in turbopuffer uses the BM25 (Best Matching 25) ranking function, a classic text search algorithm that considers query term frequency and document length, and BM25 scores documents based on how well they match query terms.\\n\\n## Benefits\\n\\nCombining vector and BM25 search produces results matching specific words or strings (i.e. product SKUs, email addresses, weighing exact keywords highly), making it useful for applications that need both semantic understanding and exact keyword matching.\\n\\n\\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"eb94cfcd-b44e-4ada-a9a0-9d8851cc22be\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:57:13.588Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Search the web for Turbopuffer BM25 full-text search documentation. I need to understand:\\n\\n1. How to enable BM25/full-text search on a Turbopuffer namespace\\n2. The API format for querying with BM25 (rank_by parameter, query syntax)\\n3. How to configure schema for BM25-indexed attributes\\n4. Whether BM25 can be combined with vector search (hybrid search)\\n5. The Turbopuffer API endpoint format for queries with BM25\\n\\nSearch for:\\n- \\\"turbopuffer bm25\\\" \\n- \\\"turbopuffer full text search\\\"\\n- \\\"turbopuffer hybrid search\\\"\\n- site:turbopuffer.com documentation\\n\\nReturn the key API details: endpoint, request format, schema configuration, and hybrid search syntax.\",\"agentId\":\"a55c0722acc8e8abd\"},\"toolUseID\":\"agent_msg_017jNnLeAo8oHu8kFtx4K1Ep\",\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_018H2DtTTXDdN6jDe1T9xPBG\",\"uuid\":\"e0611e4e-28ed-4ae9-a29c-df5120c69079\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:57:13.590Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"e0611e4e-28ed-4ae9-a29c-df5120c69079\",\