M25 scoring, configure the schema when writing documents:\\n\\n```json\\n\\\"schema\\\": {\\n  \\\"content\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"full_text_search\\\": true\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Query Syntax\\n\\nThe basic FTS query uses the `rank_by` parameter with three components:\\n\\n```\\nrank_by: [field_name, \\\"BM25\\\", query_text]\\n```\\n\\nFor example: `[\\\"content\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", \\\"turbopuffer\\\"]`\\n\\n## Filtering Results\\n\\nCombine BM25 ranking with filters using `ContainsAllTokens` to match documents containing specific terms:\\n\\n```\\nfilters: [field_name, \\\"ContainsAllTokens\\\", phrase]\\n```\\n\\nThis ensures results contain all specified tokens before ranking.\\n\\n## Supported Languages\\n\\nturbopuffer supports language-aware stemming and stopword removal for: Arabic, Danish, Dutch, English (default), Finnish, French, German, Greek, Hungarian, Italian, Norwegian, Portuguese, Romanian, Russian, Spanish, Swedish, Tamil, and Turkish.\\n\\n## Tokenization Options\\n\\nFive tokenizers are available: `word_v3` (default), `word_v2`, `word_v1`, `word_v0`, and `pre_tokenized_array` for custom client-side tokenization on `[]string` fields.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"813c56d9-693d-4298-a747-f3f4ddde0993\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:58:05.171Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Search the web for Turbopuffer BM25 full-text search documentation. I need to understand:\\n\\n1. How to enable BM25/full-text search on a Turbopuffer namespace\\n2. The API format for querying with BM25 (rank_by parameter, query syntax)\\n3. How to configure schema for BM25-indexed attributes\\n4. Whether BM25 can be combined with vector search (hybrid search)\\n5. The Turbopuffer API endpoint format for queries with BM25\\n\\nSearch for:\\n- \\\"turbopuffer bm25\\\" \\n- \\\"turbopuffer full text search\\\"\\n- \\\"turbopuffer hybrid search\\\"\\n- site:turbopuffer.com documentation\\n\\nReturn the key API details: endpoin