nd Full-Text Search\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\nHybrid search merges vector search with BM25 full-text search to capture both semantic relevance and exact keyword matches. As the documentation states: \\\"Combining them produces semantically relevant search results (vectors), as well as results matching specific words or strings (i.e. product SKUs, email addresses, weighing exact keywords highly).\\\"\\n\\n## Implementation Approach\\n\\nThe strategy involves using **rank fusion and re-ranking** in your application logic rather than within turbopuffer itself:\\n\\n1. **Separate queries**: Execute both a vector search and BM25 query independently\\n2. **Rank fusion**: Combine results using algorithms like reciprocal rank fusion\\n3. **Re-ranking**: Apply a specialized re-ranker to improve final ordering\\n\\n## API Format\\n\\nUse the `multi_query` endpoint to execute both searches in a single call:\\n\\n```python\\nresponse = ns.multi_query(\\n  queries=[\\n    {\\\"rank_by\\\": (\\\"vector\\\", \\\"ANN\\\", embedding), \\\"top_k\\\": 10},\\n    {\\\"rank_by\\\": (\\\"content\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", query_text), \\\"top_k\\\": 10}\\n  ]\\n)\\n```\\n\\n## Key Recommendation\\n\\nThe documentation advises: \\\"Keep search logic in `{search.py, search.ts}`. Use turbopuffer for initial retrieval to narrow millions of results to dozens for rank fusion and re-ranking.\\\" This separation ensures flexibility in fusion strategies while maintaining performance through efficient initial filtering.\"}]},\"uuid\":\"464a0b99-78a8-4da3-90f0-19f52333c3a8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:58:08.381Z\"},\"normalizedMessages\":[],\"type\":\"agent_progress\",\"prompt\":\"Search the web for Turbopuffer BM25 full-text search documentation. I need to understand:\\n\\n1. How to enable BM25/full-text search on a Turbopuffer namespace\\n2. The API format for querying with BM25 (rank_by parameter, query syntax)\\n3. How to configure schema for BM25-indexed attributes\\n4. Whether BM25 can be combined wit