p_k\\\": 10\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Response includes:**\\n- `rows`: Matched documents ordered by ranking score\\n- `$dist`: BM25 relevance score for each result\\n- `billing` & `performance`: Usage metrics\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. Schema Configuration for BM25-Indexed Attributes\\n\\n**Minimal configuration:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"text\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"full_text_search\\\": true\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**Advanced configuration with tuning parameters:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"text\\\": {\\n    \\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\",\\n    \\\"full_text_search\\\": {\\n      \\\"tokenizer\\\": \\\"word_v3\\\",           // Default: word_v3 (also v0, v1, v2, pre_tokenized_array)\\n      \\\"case_sensitive\\\": false,           // Default: false\\n      \\\"language\\\": \\\"english\\\",             // Supports 18 languages\\n      \\\"stemming\\\": false,                 // Default: false\\n      \\\"remove_stopwords\\\": false,         // Default: false\\n      \\\"ascii_folding\\\": false,            // Default: false\\n      \\\"max_token_length\\\": 39,            // Default: 39 (1-254 bytes)\\n      \\\"k1\\\": 1.2,                         // BM25 parameter (term frequency saturation)\\n      \\\"b\\\": 0.75,                         // BM25 parameter (length bias)\\n      \\\"k3\\\": 0                            // BM25 parameter (query term frequency)\\n    },\\n    \\\"filterable\\\": false                  // BM25 attributes non-filterable by default\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**BM25 Tuning Parameters:**\\n- **k1** (default 1.2): Controls term frequency saturation. Decrease for tweets/short text, increase for long documents.\\n- **b** (default 0.75): Controls length bias normalization. Decrease for short texts, increase for long documents.\\n- **k3** (default 0): Query term frequency parameter.\\n\\n**Note:** BM25-enabled attributes are non-filterable by default for optimization, but can be made filterable with `\\\"filterable\\\": true`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n#