entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a680cc5e-06bc-4b55-b4b6-38f7b2fa7e61\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01Narxmg3jgQAkME55Ukrufm\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_012LNwz4ZjmJPpEvKBWUwi8V\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Enable BM25 Full-Text Search + Hybrid Search in Turbopuffer\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCurrently checkpoint search is semantic-only (OpenAI embeddings → Turbopuffer cosine similarity). There's a TODO in `turbopuffer.ts` line 4 to add BM25 full-text search. BM25 excels at exact keyword matches (file names, function names, error messages) where semantic search can miss. Combining both gives the best results.\\n\\nTurbopuffer supports BM25 via a `schema` declaration on upsert and a `rank_by` query parameter. The `text` attribute already contains the searchable content — we just need to declare it as `full_text_search: true` and update queries.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | Add schema to upserts, switch search to hybrid (vector + BM25 via reciprocal rank fusion) |\\n| `api/scripts/test-search-index.ts` | Add schema to upsert, add BM25 + hybrid verification |\\n| `api/scripts/backfill-search.ts` | Add schema to upsert so backfilled data also gets BM25-indexed |\\n\\nNo route or frontend changes needed — the search endpoint already calls `searchCheckpoints()` and the hybrid improvement is transparent to callers.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n### 1. `turbopuffer.ts` — Upsert with schema\\n\\nAdd `schema` to `indexCheckpoints()` upsert payload so the `text` attribute is BM25-indexed:\\n\\n```typescript\\nbody: JSON.stringify({\\n  upserts,\\n  distance_metric: \\\"cosine_distance\\\",\\n  schema: {\\n    text: {\\n      type: \\\"string\\\",\\n      full_text_search: {\\n        language: \\\"english\\\",\\n        stemming: true,\\n        remove_stopwords: true,\\n      },\\n    },\\n  },\\n}),\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `turbopuffer.ts` — Hybrid search in `searchCheckpoints()`\\n\\nReplace the single vector query with two parallel queries (vector + BM25), then merge via reciprocal rank fusion:\\n\\n1. Fire both queries in parallel using `Promise.all`:\\n   - **Vector query**: existing cosine similarity search (needs OpenAI embedding)\\n   - **BM25 query**: `rank_by: [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", query]` (no embedding needed, just the raw query string)\\n2. Merge results using **reciprocal rank fusion (RRF)**: `score = 1/(k + rank)` with k=60 (standard constant)\\n3. Return deduplicated, merged checkpoint IDs ordered by combined score\\n\\nThe BM25 query uses the v2 namespace query endpoint (`/v2/namespaces/:ns/query`) while the vector query stays on v1. Both return checkpoint_id attributes.\\n\\nNote: The existing hardcoded namespace in `searchCheckpoints()` (`checkpoints-5be1c302-...`) will be kept as-is since the TODO says to make it dynamic later. BM25 will use the same namespace.\\n\\n### 3. `backfill-search.ts` — Add schema to backfill upserts\\n\\nThe backfill script uses the `@turbopuffer/turbopuffer` SDK's `ns.upsert()`. Add the schema config so backfilled data also gets BM25-indexed. The SDK supports passing schema in the upsert call.\\n\\n### 4. `test-search-index.ts` — Update test script\\n\\nAdd schema to the upsert call and add a BM25 search verification step after the existing vector search verification.\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Run `npx tsx scripts/test-search-index.ts --limit 5` — confirm upsert succeeds with schema\\n2. Test BM25 search: query for an exact file name or keyword that appears in checkpoint text\\n3. Test hybrid search: query should return results combining both exact matches and semantic matches\\n4. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` — type check passes\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":290,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":124432,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":290},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYidcA9KYjLLYJZ9Hqdy8\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"10ce8f18-9974-4302-846f-a2727ddb0318\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:59:01.161Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"10ce8f18-9974-4302-846f-a2727ddb0318\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a680cc5e-06bc-4b55-b4b6-38f7b2fa7e61\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"<tool_use_error>File has not been read yet. Read it first before writing to it.</tool_use_error>\",\"is_error\":true,\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_012LNwz4ZjmJPpEvKBWUwi8V\"}]},\"uuid\":\"73075500-98d3-4114-b6fd-4ba9009d8ca8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:59:01.161Z\",\"toolUseResult\":\"Error: File has not been read yet. Read it first before writing to it.\",\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"10ce8f18-9974-4302-846f-a2727ddb0318\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"73075500-98d3-4114-b6fd-4ba9009d8ca8\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a680cc5e-06bc-4b55-b4b6-38f7b2fa7e61\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_017WvhW1adYoUdNttWaa5MpV\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_019maym6XrRMsdn9vVkDqeTq\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,