 up for other flows).\\n     6→\\n     7→## Approach\\n     8→\\n     9→Add a new `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` Cloudflare Queue. After checkpoint data is upserted into PlanetScale (in both `processSessionsPushEvent` and `processCommitPushEvent`), send a lightweight message to the queue. A new queue consumer fetches checkpoint data from PlanetScale, embeds search text via OpenAI, and upserts vectors to Turbopuffer.\\n    10→\\n    11→## Files to Modify\\n    12→\\n    13→| File | Action | Description |\\n    14→|------|--------|-------------|\\n    15→| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | **Create** | Message type, type guard, batch processor |\\n    16→| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Modify** | Add `indexCheckpoints()` function (embed + upsert) |\\n    17→| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue` |\\n    18→| `api/wrangler.jsonc` | **Modify** | Add queue producer + consumer (staging & production) |\\n    19→| `api/src/index.ts` | **Modify** | Add queue consumer branch for search index messages |\\n    20→| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | **Modify** | Enqueue after upsert in both push event handlers |\\n    21→\\n    22→## Implementation Details\\n    23→\\n    24→### 1. Search Index Queue (`api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`)\\n    25→\\n    26→Follow existing `RepoSyncMessage` / `UserRepoSyncMessage` pattern from `repo-sync-queue.ts` and `user-repo-sync.ts`.\\n    27→\\n    28→```typescript\\n    29→export interface SearchIndexMessage {\\n    30→  repoId: string;\\n    31→  checkpointIds: string[];\\n    32→  queuedAt: string;\\n    33→}\\n    34→\\n    35→export function isSearchIndexMessage(msg: unknown): msg is SearchIndexMessage { ... }\\n    36→\\n    37→export async function processSearchIndexBatch(\\n    38→  batch: MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n    39→  env: Env,\\n    40→): Promise<void> { ... }\\n    41→```\\n    42→\\n    43→**Batch processor flow per message:**\\n    44→1. Early return if `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY` missing — `msg.ack()` + warning log\\n    45→2. Fetch checkpoint + commit data from PlanetScale via `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n    46→3. Build search text per checkpoint (same format as `buildSearchText()` in backfill script)\\n    47→4. Call `indexCheckpoints()` from turbopuffer.ts\\n    48→5. Success → `msg.ack()`, transient failure → `msg.retry()`\\n    49→\\n    50→Logging follows `[search-index-queue]` prefix pattern, with batch metrics matching `repo-sync-queue.ts`.\\n    51→\\n    52→### 2. Turbopuffer Indexing Function (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n    53→\\n    54→Add `indexCheckpoints()` alongside existing `searchCheckpoints()`:\\n    55→\\n    56→```typescript\\n    57→export async function indexCheckpoints(\\n    58→  turbopufferApiKey: string,\\n    59→  openaiApiKey: string,\\n    60→  repoId: string,\\n    61→  checkpoints: Array<{\\n    62→    checkpoint_id: string;\\n    63→    branch: string | null;\\n    64→    agent: string | null;\\n    65→    commit_author_username: string | null;\\n    66→    created_at: string | null;\\n    67→    commit_sha: string | null;\\n    68→    commit_message: string | null;\\n    69→    prompt: string | null;\\n    70→    files_touched: string[] | null;\\n    71→  }>,\\n    72→): Promise<number>\\n    73→```\\n    74→\\n    75→- Build search text: `Prompt: ...\\\\nCommit: ...\\\\nFiles: ...` (same as backfill `buildSearchText()`)\\n    76→- Embed via OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dims) — batch all texts in one call\\n    77→- Upsert to Turbopuffer `POST /v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repoId}/upsert` with same attributes as backfill\\n    78→- Use deterministic numeric IDs from checkpoint_id hash (consistent with potential re-indexing)\\n    79→- Returns count of successfully indexed checkpoints\\n    80→\\n    81→### 3. Env Binding (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n    82→\\n    83→```typescript\\n    84→SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue;  // Optional — indexing skipped if not configured