 Currently indexing only happens via the backfill script. When new checkpoints arrive via GitHub webhooks, they need to be indexed in Turbopuffer in real-time. The indexing must be async and non-blocking to the webhook processing pipeline, using Cloudflare Queues (already set up for other flows).\\n\\n## Approach\\n\\nAdd a new `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` Cloudflare Queue. After checkpoint data is upserted into PlanetScale (in both `processSessionsPushEvent` and `processCommitPushEvent`), send a lightweight message to the queue. A new queue consumer fetches checkpoint data from PlanetScale, embeds search text via OpenAI, and upserts vectors to Turbopuffer.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Action | Description |\\n|------|--------|-------------|\\n| `api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts` | **Create** | Message type, type guard, batch processor |\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | **Modify** | Add `indexCheckpoints()` function (embed + upsert) |\\n| `api/src/env.ts` | **Modify** | Add optional `SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue` |\\n| `api/wrangler.jsonc` | **Modify** | Add queue producer + consumer (staging & production) |\\n| `api/src/index.ts` | **Modify** | Add queue consumer branch for search index messages |\\n| `api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts` | **Modify** | Enqueue after upsert in both push event handlers |\\n\\n## Implementation Details\\n\\n### 1. Search Index Queue (`api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts`)\\n\\nFollow existing `RepoSyncMessage` / `UserRepoSyncMessage` pattern from `repo-sync-queue.ts` and `user-repo-sync.ts`.\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport interface SearchIndexMessage {\\n  repoId: string;\\n  checkpointIds: string[];\\n  queuedAt: string;\\n}\\n\\nexport function isSearchIndexMessage(msg: unknown): msg is SearchIndexMessage { ... }\\n\\nexport async function processSearchIndexBatch(\\n  batch: MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n  env: Env,\\n): Promise<void> { ... }\\n```\\n\\n**Batch processor flow per message:**\\n1. Early return if `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` or `OPENAI_API_KEY` missing — `msg.ack()` + warning log\\n2. Fetch checkpoint + commit data from PlanetScale via `db.checkpoints.getByIds(repoId, checkpointIds)`\\n3. Build search text per checkpoint (same format as `buildSearchText()` in backfill script)\\n4. Call `indexCheckpoints()` from turbopuffer.ts\\n5. Success → `msg.ack()`, transient failure → `msg.retry()`\\n\\nLogging follows `[search-index-queue]` prefix pattern, with batch metrics matching `repo-sync-queue.ts`.\\n\\n### 2. Turbopuffer Indexing Function (`api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts`)\\n\\nAdd `indexCheckpoints()` alongside existing `searchCheckpoints()`:\\n\\n```typescript\\nexport async function indexCheckpoints(\\n  turbopufferApiKey: string,\\n  openaiApiKey: string,\\n  repoId: string,\\n  checkpoints: Array<{\\n    checkpoint_id: string;\\n    branch: string | null;\\n    agent: string | null;\\n    commit_author_username: string | null;\\n    created_at: string | null;\\n    commit_sha: string | null;\\n    commit_message: string | null;\\n    prompt: string | null;\\n    files_touched: string[] | null;\\n  }>,\\n): Promise<number>\\n```\\n\\n- Build search text: `Prompt: ...\\\\nCommit: ...\\\\nFiles: ...` (same as backfill `buildSearchText()`)\\n- Embed via OpenAI `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dims) — batch all texts in one call\\n- Upsert to Turbopuffer `POST /v1/vectors/checkpoints-{repoId}/upsert` with same attributes as backfill\\n- Use deterministic numeric IDs from checkpoint_id hash (consistent with potential re-indexing)\\n- Returns count of successfully indexed checkpoints\\n\\n### 3. Env Binding (`api/src/env.ts`)\\n\\n```typescript\\nSEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE?: Queue;  // Optional — indexing skipped if not configured\\n```\\n\\nOptional so existing environments without the queue continue working.\\n\\n### 4. Wrangler Config (`api/wrangler.jsonc`)\\n\\n**Staging (default):**\\n```jsonc\\n// In producers array:\\n{ \\\"binding\\\": \\\"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\\\", \\\"queue\\\": \\\"partialto-api-search-index\\\" }\\n// In consumers array:\\n{ \\\"queue\\\": \\\"partialto-api-search-index\\\", \\\"max_retries\\\": 3, \\\"max_batch_size\\\": 10, \\\"max_batch_timeout\\\": 5 }\\n```\\n\\n**Production (`env.production`):**\\n```jsonc\\n// In producers array:\\n{ \\\"binding\\\": \\\"SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE\\\", \\\"queue\\\": \\\"entireio-api-search-index\\\" }\\n// In consumers array:\\n{ \\\"queue\\\": \\\"entireio-api-search-index\\\", \\\"max_retries\\\": 3, \\\"max_batch_size\\\": 10, \\\"max_batch_timeout\\\": 5 }\\n```\\n\\n### 5. Queue Consumer Routing (`api/src/index.ts`)\\n\\nAdd new branch in `queue()` handler at line ~193, before the unknown-message fallback:\\n\\n```typescript\\n} else if (firstMessage && isSearchIndexMessage(firstMessage)) {\\n  await processSearchIndexBatch(\\n    batch as MessageBatch<SearchIndexMessage>,\\n    env,\\n  );\\n}\\n```\\n\\nImport `SearchIndexMessage`, `isSearchIndexMessage`, `processSearchIndexBatch` from `../lib/search-index-queue`.\\n\\n### 6. Enqueue in Webhook Processing (`api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts`)\\n\\n**In `processSessionsPushEvent()`** — after line 965 (`db.checkpoints.upsertBatch` succeeds):\\n```typescript\\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\\n    checkpointIds,\\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**In `processCommitPushEvent()`** — after line 1220 (`db.checkpoints.upsertCommitBatch` succeeds):\\n```typescript\\nif (env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE) {\\n  await env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE.send({\\n    repoId: repoRecord.id,\\n    checkpointIds: checkpointCommits.map((c) => c.checkpointId),\\n    queuedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\\n  } satisfies SearchIndexMessage);\\n}\\n```\\n\\nBoth are guarded by `env.SEARCH_INDEX_QUEUE` — if the binding isn't configured, webhook processing is unaffected. The `send()` call is fast (queue is local to the worker) and non-blocking to the webhook response.\\n\\n## Key Design Decisions\\n\\n- **Optional everything**: Queue binding, API keys — graceful degradation at every level\\n- **Fetch from DB in consumer, not in message**: Keeps messages small, ensures latest data is indexed\\n- **Same vector format as backfill**: Text construction and attributes match `backfill-search.ts` exactly\\n- **`msg.ack()` on missing API keys**: Don't retry messages that can never succeed\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Create queue: `wrangler queues create partialto-api-search-index`\\n2. Set secrets: `TURBOPUFFER_API_KEY` and `OPENAI_API_KEY` via `wrangler secret put`\\n3. Deploy, then push a commit with an `Entire-Checkpoint` trailer\\n4. Check worker logs for `[search-index-queue]` entries\\n5. Search for the new checkpoint via the search endpoint to confirm it was indexed\\n\",\"numLines\":162,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":162}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"207e8d91-d5a3-4ca1-9e43-1bb07792c233\"}\n{\"type\":\"file-history-snapshot\",\"messageId\":\"cc66f9fc-1117-46f0-9b50-0ea74ca1f92e\",\"snapshot\":{\"messageId\":\"2949a422-c60a-40f5-a238-4cc198bffdd8\",\"trackedFileBackups\":{\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/lib/search-index-queue.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"58b103778b10e1de@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:33:47.082Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"cfe3cf9f80a2a907@v3\",\"version\":3,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:44:52.421Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/env.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"71fd94ed958a53c5@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:33:47.082Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/wrangler.jsonc\":{\"backupFileName\":\"107d6f4ab690967c@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:33:47.082Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/index.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"f7eaaeacbdcbdf4d@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:33:47.083Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/src/lib/webhook/processing.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"85e4a27c2afbe3bd@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:33:47.083Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/entire.io/api/scripts/test-search-index.ts\":{\"backupFileName\":\"9b482142b47d3898@v2\",\"version\":2,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:44:52.421Z\"},\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\":{\"backupFileName\":\"cdbadcbe5f5d68a2@v1\",\"version\":1,\"backupTime\":\"2026-03-04T19:59:23.616Z\"}},\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:56:50.298Z\"},\"isSnapshotUpdate\":true}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"41eaba95-b345-41a1-833a-fb4ca9645cf5\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a680cc5e-06bc-4b55-b4b6-38f7b2fa7e61\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main\",\"slug\":\"resilient-squishing-fern\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01NBaA8TKTreXaS2SkKQSr2o\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01EnqJJvnzDTzTcobFzK9EwT\",\"name\":\"Write\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/.claude/plans/resilient-squishing-fern.md\",\"content\":\"# Enable BM25 Full-Text Search + Hybrid Search in Turbopuffer\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoint search is currently semantic-only (OpenAI embeddings → Turbopuffer cosine similarity). There's a TODO in `turbopuffer.ts:4` to add BM25 full-text search. BM25 excels at exact keyword matches (file names, function names, error messages) where semantic search can miss. Adding both and combining via rank fusion gives the best results.\\n\\nTurbopuffer supports BM25 natively via a `schema` declaration on upsert (`full_text_search: true` on string attributes) and a `rank_by` query parameter. The `text` attribute already contains the searchable content — we just need to declare it as full-text-searchable and update queries.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | Add schema to upserts, replace single vector query with hybrid (vector + BM25 via reciprocal rank fusion) |\\n| `api/scripts/test-search-index.ts` | Add schema to upsert, add BM25 + hybrid verification steps |\\n| `api/scripts/backfill-search.ts` | Add schema to SDK upsert call so backfilled data is BM25-indexed |\\n\\nNo route, frontend, or env changes needed — `searchCheckpoints()` signature stays the same, hybrid is transparent to callers.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n### 1. `turbopuffer.ts` — Add schema to `indexCheckpoints()` upsert\\n\\nAdd a `schema` field to the upsert request body so the `text` attribute gets BM25-indexed:\\n\\n```typescript\\nbody: JSON.stringify({\\n  upserts,\\n  distance_metric: \\\"cosine_distance\\\",\\n  schema: {\\n    text: {\\n      type: \\\"string\\\",\\n      full_text_search: {\\n        language: \\\"english\\\",\\n        stemming: true,\\n        remove_stopwords: true,\\n      },\\n    },\\n  },\\n}),\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `turbopuffer.ts` — Replace `searchCheckpoints()` with hybrid search\\n\\nCurrent: single vector cosine query on v1 API.\\n\\nNew: fire vector + BM25 in parallel, merge via reciprocal rank fusion.\\n\\n```\\nVector query (v1):  POST /v1/vectors/:ns/query  { vector, top_k, distance_metric, include_attributes }\\nBM25 query (v2):    POST /v2/namespaces/:ns/query  { rank_by: [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", query], top_k, include_attributes }\\n```\\n\\nBoth use the same hardcoded namespace (`checkpoints-5be1c302-...`) as the existing code.\\n\\n**Merge strategy — Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF):**\\n```\\nscore(doc) = 1/(k + rank_vector) + 1/(k + rank_bm25)   where k=60\\n```\\n- Documents appearing in both result sets get boosted\\n- Documents only in one set still appear but ranked lower\\n- k=60 is the standard constant that prevents top-ranked items from dominating\\n\\nThe function signature stays identical — callers see no change. `openaiApiKey` is still required for the vector half of the hybrid query. The BM25 query needs only the turbopuffer key and raw query text (no embedding).\\n\\n### 3. `backfill-search.ts` — Add schema to backfill upserts\\n\\nThe backfill uses the `@turbopuffer/turbopuffer` SDK. Add schema to the `ns.upsert()` call:\\n\\n```typescript\\nawait ns.upsert({\\n  vectors,\\n  distance_metric: \\\"cosine_distance\\\",\\n  schema: {\\n    text: {\\n      type: \\\"string\\\",\\n      full_text_search: {\\n        language: \\\"english\\\",\\n        stemming: true,\\n        remove_stopwords: true,\\n      },\\n    },\\n  },\\n});\\n```\\n\\n### 4. `test-search-index.ts` — Update test script\\n\\n- Add schema to the upsert call\\n- Add BM25 search verification step (query an exact keyword)\\n- Add hybrid verification showing combined results\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Delete the test namespace: `curl -X DELETE` (to start fresh with new schema)\\n2. Run `npx tsx scripts/test-search-index.ts --limit 5` — confirm upsert + schema works\\n3. Verify BM25 results return for exact keyword queries\\n4. Verify hybrid results combine both semantic and keyword matches\\n5. Run `npx tsc --noEmit` — type check passes\\n\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2617,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":125940,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2617},\"output_tokens\":25,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYideFnhreoMRE4uF9VXd\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"cc66f9fc-1117-46f0-9b50-0ea74ca1f92e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T19:59:23.613Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"cc66f9fc-1117-46f0-9b50-0ea74ca1f92e\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/evisdrenova/code/entire/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a680cc5e-06bc-4b55-b4b6-38f7b2fa7e61\",\"version\":\"2.1.56\",\"gitBranch\":\"main