\",\"id\":\"msg_01WwtyseW9pJx2MtwHNCzhSh\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_017y5gJQ1xvVZAFvYAGc8TS7\",\"name\":\"ExitPlanMode\",\"input\":{\"plan\":\"# Enable BM25 Full-Text Search + Hybrid Search in Turbopuffer\\n\\n## Context\\n\\nCheckpoint search is currently semantic-only (OpenAI embeddings → Turbopuffer cosine similarity). There's a TODO in `turbopuffer.ts:4` to add BM25 full-text search. BM25 excels at exact keyword matches (file names, function names, error messages) where semantic search can miss. Adding both and combining via rank fusion gives the best results.\\n\\nTurbopuffer supports BM25 natively via a `schema` declaration on upsert (`full_text_search: true` on string attributes) and a `rank_by` query parameter. The `text` attribute already contains the searchable content — we just need to declare it as full-text-searchable and update queries.\\n\\n## Files to Modify\\n\\n| File | Change |\\n|------|--------|\\n| `api/src/lib/turbopuffer.ts` | Add schema to upserts, replace single vector query with hybrid (vector + BM25 via reciprocal rank fusion) |\\n| `api/scripts/test-search-index.ts` | Add schema to upsert, add BM25 + hybrid verification steps |\\n| `api/scripts/backfill-search.ts` | Add schema to SDK upsert call so backfilled data is BM25-indexed |\\n\\nNo route, frontend, or env changes needed — `searchCheckpoints()` signature stays the same, hybrid is transparent to callers.\\n\\n## Implementation\\n\\n### 1. `turbopuffer.ts` — Add schema to `indexCheckpoints()` upsert\\n\\nAdd a `schema` field to the upsert request body so the `text` attribute gets BM25-indexed:\\n\\n```typescript\\nbody: JSON.stringify({\\n  upserts,\\n  distance_metric: \\\"cosine_distance\\\",\\n  schema: {\\n    text: {\\n      type: \\\"string\\\",\\n      full_text_search: {\\n        language: \\\"english\\\",\\n        stemming: true,\\n        remove_stopwords: true,\\n      },\\n    },\\n  },\\n}),\\n```\\n\\n### 2. `turbopuffer.ts` — Replace `searchCheckpoints()` with hybrid search\\n\\nCurrent: single vector cosine query on v1 API.\\n\\nNew: fire vector + BM25 in parallel, merge via reciprocal rank fusion.\\n\\n```\\nVector query (v1):  POST /v1/vectors/:ns/query  { vector, top_k, distance_metric, include_attributes }\\nBM25 query (v2):    POST /v2/namespaces/:ns/query  { rank_by: [\\\"text\\\", \\\"BM25\\\", query], top_k, include_attributes }\\n```\\n\\nBoth use the same hardcoded namespace (`checkpoints-5be1c302-...`) as the existing code.\\n\\n**Merge strategy — Reciprocal Rank Fusion (RRF):**\\n```\\nscore(doc) = 1/(k + rank_vector) + 1/(k + rank_bm25)   where k=60\\n```\\n- Documents appearing in both result sets get boosted\\n- Documents only in one set still appear but ranked lower\\n- k=60 is the standard constant that prevents top-ranked items from dominating\\n\\nThe function signature stays identical — callers see no change. `openaiApiKey` is still required for the vector half of the hybrid query. The BM25 query needs only the turbopuffer key and raw query text (no embedding).\\n\\n### 3. `backfill-search.ts` — Add schema to backfill upserts\\n\\nThe backfill uses the `@turbopuffer/turbopuffer` SDK. Add schema to the `ns.upsert()` call:\\n\\n```typescript\\nawait ns.upsert({\\n  vectors,\\n  distance_metric: \\\"cosine_distance\\\",\\n  schema: {\\n    text: {\\n      type: \\\"string\\\",\\n      full_text_search: {\\n        language: \\\"english\\\",\\n        stemming: true,\\n        remove_stopwords: true,\\n      },\\n    },\\n  },\\n});\\n```\\n\\n### 4. `test-search-index.ts` — Update test script\\n\\n- Add schema to the upsert call\\n- Add BM25 search verification step (query an exact keyword)\\n- Add hybrid verification showing combined results\\n\\n## Verification\\n\\n1. Delete the test namespace: `curl -X DELETE` (to start fresh with new schema)\\n2. Run `npx tsx scripts/test-search-index.ts --limit 5` — confirm upsert + schema works\\n3. 